Trader Joe's and Aldi were started by brothers in Germany. One wanted to sell cigarettes, the other did not, so they split the company. Both appear to have done well in the US, although you see more Aldis than TJs. Mostly carry their own private brands, which are often made by the name brand companies. I buy stuff from both, but rarely. 

